<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued April 23 at 2:39AM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 330 AM CDT
FOR BEAVER...EASTERN TEXAS...LIPSCOMB...HUTCHINSON...HANSFORD...
SOUTHEASTERN SHERMAN...ROBERTS...HEMPHILL...OCHILTREE AND EASTERN
MOORE COUNTIES...
At 239 AM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 5 miles northwest of Hayne to near Baker to 8 miles
west of Stinnett, moving northeast at 55 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Borger, Perryton, Spearman, Lipscomb, Canadian, Beaver, Miami,
Fritch, Hooker, Stinnett, Booker, Gruver, Tyrone, Forgan, Follett,
Higgins, Optima, Darrouzett, Hardesty and Sanford.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
